<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-12-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-12-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="766" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d766">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.01/526</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Acting Chairman of the Special Trade Delegation
                                of the Far Eastern Republic to the United States</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Skvirsky</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-12-04"><hi rend="italic">December 4,
                                1922</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to advise you that the
                            National Assembly of the Far Eastern Republic at its session on November
                            12th., 1922 <pb facs="0982" n="868" xml:id="pg_868"/> at Chita had
                            unanimously voted to amalgamate with the Russian Socialist Federated
                            Soviet Republic.</p>
                        <p>I avail myself of this occasion to express the hope of the people of the
                            Russian Far East for a closer unity between the peoples of Russia and
                            United States of America.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">B. Skvirsky</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>